Subinterfaces of ControlConstruct in org.mindswap.owls.process
 interface AnyOrder
          AnyOrder consists of a bag of processes which are executed in any order, i.e., without precedence order (but not concurrently).
 interface AsProcess
          AsProcess turns an arbitrary control construct into a "local process" that is called at the point it is defined.
 interface Choice
          Choice consists of a bag of control constructs from which one and only one construct (whose preconditions are satisfied) is chosen for execution.
 interface CollectionControlConstruct
          Just another layer of abstraction for control constructs that are either based on bags (such as AnyOrder or Split), or lists (such as Sequence).
 interface ForEach
           
 interface IfThenElse
          An If-Then-Else is a binary branching construct.
 interface Iterate
          This is super interface for loop based control constructs such as RepeatUntil, RepeatWhile, and the non OWL-S standard ForEach.
 interface Perform
          Corresponding OWL-S concept: org.mindswap.owls.vocabulary.OWLS.Process#Perform

 interface Sequence
          Sequence is a chain of constructs which is executed sequentially one after another, according to the order of the constructs.
 interface Set
           
 interface Split
          Split consists of a bag of processes which are executed concurrently.
 interface SplitJoin
          Split-join consists of a bag of processes which are executed concurrently.
